metadata.name: Η αποκαθήλωση της Αφροδίτης
metadata.description:
Aphrodite/Venus (Αφροδίτη) was goddess of love, beauty, pleasure and procreation in Greek mythology. She was the wellspring of both homosexual and heterosexual erotic desire as well as being known for her generously nurturing and passionately destructive persona.

Aphrodite generously rewarded those who honored her, but also punished those who disrespected her, often quite brutally.

Now she is standing there. In melancholy, watching the storm coming towards her. The Descent of a goddess.

JPEG 6000x4000
300 DPI
Captured back on the 3rd of August 2018
